        "explanation": "Matrix multiplication is distributive over addition, so $A(B+C) = AB + AC$ whenever the dimensions allow the products to be defined."
      },
      {
        "type": "mcq",
        "question": "Solve for $x$: $x + y = 10, y = x$.",
